solution.p:
Substitute (2,-1) for (x_1,y_1) and (4,3) for (x_2,y_2) in the distance formula to obtain
	\begin{aligned}
                d \amp = \sqrt{(x_2-x_1)^2+(y_2-y_1)^2}\\
                	\amp = \sqrt{(4-2)^2+[3-(-1)]^2}\\
                 	\amp = \sqrt{4+16} =\sqrt{20} \approx 4.47                
                \end{aligned}

note.p:
In Example 1 we obtain the same answer if we use (4,3) for P_1 and (2,-1) for P_2:
	\begin{aligned}
                d \amp = \sqrt{(2-4)^2+[(-1)-3]^2}\\
                 	\amp = \sqrt{4+16} =\sqrt{20}                
                \end{aligned}

solution.p:
The radius is the distance from the center to either of the endpoints of the diameter, say the point (7,5). We use the distance formula with the points (7,5) and (4,2) to find the radius.
	\begin{aligned}
                r \amp = \sqrt{(7-4)^2+(5-2)^2}\\
                \amp = \sqrt{3^2+3^2}=\sqrt{18}   
                \end{aligned} 
Finally, we substitute 4 forh and 2 for k (the coordinates of the center) and \sqrt{18} for r (the radius) into the standard form 
	(x-h)^2+(y-k)^2=r^2
to obtain 
	(x-4)^2+(y-2)^2=18
